{"parse":{"title":"Menstrual leave","pageid":32069520,"revid":841695209,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>Menstrual leave</b> is a type of <a href=\"/wiki/Leave_of_absence\" title=\"Leave of absence\">leave</a> where a <a href=\"/wiki/Woman\" title=\"Woman\">woman</a> may have the option to take paid or unpaid leave from her employment if she is <a href=\"/wiki/Menstruating\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Menstruating\">menstruating</a> and is unable to go to work because of this.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> Menstrual leave is controversial because it is seen by some as a criticism of women's work efficiency or as <a href=\"/wiki/Sexism\" title=\"Sexism\">sexism</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#History\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">History</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Corporate_policies\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Corporate policies</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Laws\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Laws</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#External_links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External links</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"History\">History</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Menstrual_leave&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: History\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>A girls school in the south <a href=\"/wiki/India\" title=\"India\">Indian</a> state of <a href=\"/wiki/Kerala\" title=\"Kerala\">Kerala</a> had granted its students menstrual leave as early as 1912.<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The concept of menstrual leave started in <a href=\"/wiki/Japan\" title=\"Japan\">Japan</a> in the early 20th century. In the 1920s, Japanese labor unions started to demand leave (seiri kyuka) for their female workers. In 1947, a <a href=\"/wiki/Law\" title=\"Law\">law</a> was brought into force by the Japanese Labor Standards that allowed menstruating women to take days off work. Then a unique legislation of its kind, it is now found in a few countries. <a href=\"/wiki/Debate\" title=\"Debate\">Debate</a> continues as to whether it is a <a href=\"/wiki/Medical_necessity\" title=\"Medical necessity\">medical necessity</a> or a discriminatory measure.<sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Corporate_policies\">Corporate policies</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Menstrual_leave&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Corporate policies\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p><a href=\"/wiki/Nike,_Inc.\" title=\"Nike, Inc.\">Nike</a> also included menstrual leave in their <a href=\"/wiki/Code_of_Conduct\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Code of Conduct\">Code of Conduct</a> in 2007, implemented around the globe wherever they operate. Nike obliges the <a href=\"/wiki/Business_partners\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Business partners\">business partners</a> to follow the code principles by signing a <a href=\"/wiki/Memorandum_of_Understanding\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Memorandum of Understanding\">Memorandum of Understanding</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-10\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup> Australian Manufacturing Workers Union (AMWU) started a campaign for menstrual leave for female employees at <a href=\"/wiki/Toyota\" title=\"Toyota\">Toyota</a>. The union asked for 12 paid days of menstrual leave for a woman per year.<sup id=\"cite_ref-11\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Laws\">Laws</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Menstrual_leave&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Laws\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Menstrual leave policies exist in some Asian countries, although individual companies in countries that do not have national laws may choose to implement such policies.\n</p><p>In <a href=\"/wiki/Indonesia\" title=\"Indonesia\">Indonesia</a>, under the Labor Act of 1948, women have a right to two days of menstrual leave per month.<sup id=\"cite_ref-12\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-12\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In <a href=\"/wiki/Japan\" title=\"Japan\">Japan</a>,  Article 68 of the Labour Standards Law states \"When a woman for whom work during menstrual periods would be specially difficult has requested leave, the employer shall not employ such woman on days of the menstrual period.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-13\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-13\">&#91;13&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-14\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-14\">&#91;14&#93;</a></sup> While Japanese law requires that a woman going through especially difficult menstruation be allowed to take leave, it does not require companies to provide paid leave or extra pay for women who choose to work during menstruation.\n</p><p>In <a href=\"/wiki/South_Korea\" title=\"South Korea\">South Korea</a>, not only are female employees entitled to menstrual leave according to the Article 71 of the Labour Standards Law,<sup id=\"cite_ref-15\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-15\">&#91;15&#93;</a></sup> but they are also ensured additional pay if they do not take the menstrual leave that they are entitled to.<sup id=\"cite_ref-16\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-16\">&#91;16&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In <a href=\"/wiki/Taiwan\" title=\"Taiwan\">Taiwan</a>, the Act of Gender Equality in Employment gives women three days of \"menstrual leave\" per year, which will not be calculated toward the 30 days of \"common sick leave\", giving women up to 33 days of \"health-related leaves\" per year. The extra three days do not come with half-pays once a woman employee exceeds the regulated 30.<sup id=\"cite_ref-17\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-17\">&#91;17&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Menstrual_leave&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap mw-references-columns\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\">classprojects. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://classprojects.kenyon.edu/wmns/Wmns36/bloodflow/legal.htm#leave\">\"menstrual leave\"</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=menstrual+leave&amp;rft.au=classprojects&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fclassprojects.kenyon.edu%2Fwmns%2FWmns36%2Fbloodflow%2Flegal.htm%23leave&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMenstrual+leave\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\">cleanclothes. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://web.archive.org/web/20110813171350/http://cleanclothes.org/newslist/252-labour-rights-in-indonesia-what-is-menstruation-leave\">\"what is menstruation leave\"</a>. Archived from <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://cleanclothes.org/newslist/252-labour-rights-in-indonesia-what-is-menstruation-leave\">the original</a> on 2011-08-13.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=what+is+menstruation+leave&amp;rft.au=cleanclothes&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fcleanclothes.org%2Fnewslist%2F252-labour-rights-in-indonesia-what-is-menstruation-leave&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMenstrual+leave\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\">Iuliano, Sarah. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://lipmag.com/culture/menstrual-leave-delightful-or-discriminatory/\">\"Menstrual leave: delightful or discriminatory?\"</a>. <i>5 August 2013</i>. Lip Magazine<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">3 January</span> 2014</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=5+August+2013&amp;rft.atitle=Menstrual+leave%3A+delightful+or+discriminatory%3F&amp;rft.aulast=Iuliano&amp;rft.aufirst=Sarah&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Flipmag.com%2Fculture%2Fmenstrual-leave-delightful-or-discriminatory%2F&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMenstrual+leave\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation news\">Price, Catherine (11 October 2006). <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.salon.com/2006/10/11/menstruation_4/\">\"Should women get paid menstruation leave?\"</a>. <i>Salon</i><span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">3 January</span> 2014</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.jtitle=Salon&amp;rft.atitle=Should+women+get+paid+menstruation+leave%3F&amp;rft.date=2006-10-11&amp;rft.aulast=Price&amp;rft.aufirst=Catherine&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.salon.com%2F2006%2F10%2F11%2Fmenstruation_4%2F&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMenstrual+leave\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-5\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.ndtv.com/kerala-news/a-kerala-school-granted-period-leave-105-years-ago-1739698\">\"A Kerala School Granted Period Leave 105 Years Ago\"</a>. <a href=\"/wiki/NDTV\" title=\"NDTV\">NDTV</a>. 20 August 2017. Retrieved 20 August 2017.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-6\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation journal\">JSTOR. \"Japan's 1986 Equal Employment Opportunity Law and the Changing Discourse on Gender\". <b>20</b>: 268\u2013302. <a href=\"/wiki/JSTOR\" title=\"JSTOR\">JSTOR</a>&#160;<a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"//www.jstor.org/stable/3174950\">3174950</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Japan%27s+1986+Equal+Employment+Opportunity+Law+and+the+Changing+Discourse+on+Gender&amp;rft.volume=20&amp;rft.pages=268-302&amp;rft_id=%2F%2Fwww.jstor.org%2Fstable%2F3174950&amp;rft.au=JSTOR&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMenstrual+leave\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-7\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-7\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\">HARVARD UNIVERSITY, 2007. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://gradworks.umi.com/32/65/3265147.html\">\"Periodic struggles: Menstruation leave in modern Japan\"</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Periodic+struggles%3A+Menstruation+leave+in+modern+Japan&amp;rft.au=HARVARD+UNIVERSITY%2C+2007&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fgradworks.umi.com%2F32%2F65%2F3265147.html&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMenstrual+leave\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-8\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-8\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external free\" href=\"https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2014/may/24/women-menstrual-leave-menopause-equality-biology-not-destiny\">https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2014/may/24/women-menstrual-leave-menopause-equality-biology-not-destiny</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-9\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-9\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external free\" href=\"https://www.theatlantic.com/health/archive/2014/05/should-women-get-paid-menstrual-leave-days/370789/\">https://www.theatlantic.com/health/archive/2014/05/should-women-get-paid-menstrual-leave-days/370789/</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-10\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-10\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\">apparelsearch. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.apparelsearch.com/education/research/child_labor_clothing/child_labor_fashion_industry_2005/V_Apparel_Appendices/Surveys_from_companies/Nike.htm\">\"NIKE Policy\"</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=NIKE+Policy&amp;rft.au=apparelsearch&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.apparelsearch.com%2Feducation%2Fresearch%2Fchild_labor_clothing%2Fchild_labor_fashion_industry_2005%2FV_Apparel_Appendices%2FSurveys_from_companies%2FNike.htm&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AMenstrual+leave\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display:none;\">&#160;</span></span></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-11\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-11\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\">abc. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.abc.net.au/news/newsitems/200502/s1300583.htm\">\"Unions seek 'menstrual leave' for Toyota workers\"</a>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rf